title: For Sale/Trade:  Mossberg 500AB 12-gauge w/scope 6-shot pump shotgun 30" barrel
postcontent:
This is the Mossberg 500AB, with a picatinny rail mounted Red Dot scope (Pics of shotgun with scope will be posted later this evening). The 500AB is the 500A Mossberg shotgun with some upgrades...specifically a Walnut stock VS the various hardwood stocks found on the regular 500A model. This 500AB also has some metal etchings ,as seen in 1 photo, that the 500A doesnt have ...and it has a 30" barrel. (Every part on this 500AB is interchangeable with the regular 500A)
This is a fixed full choke 30" barreled shotgun. 30 inches is a long range shotgun. Perfect for Deer and Water Fowl...and predators of any nature. You get the 75-100 yard reach of a rifle, with the spread pattern of a shotgun. Full choke means it keeps it's shot pattern tight over a long distance, so you get killing/stopping power at rifle like distances. It shoots bird and buck shot...and rifled slugs. It is chambered for 2 and 3/4" and 3.00" shells. It functions flawlessly and it looks good. The bore is beautiful inside...slick as a whistle. It also has a metal safety switch, not a plastic one like the newer Mossbergs. It has a Tasco Red Dot scope, a good one, that enables quick sholdering and accurate firing of shotgun. For those folks who don't know what a Red Dot scope is: You turn the switch on and the red dot is displayed in the scope lens...when you look thru the scope, wherever the dot is - is where the bullet goes. If you move your head, the red dot stays on the target your pointing at and you can still see the dot as you move your head around. It makes for very quick and accurate shooting). I love this shotgun, and the new owner will too. I will trade this gun.

Dear (House Judiciary Committee Member Name),

Please oppose House Bill 1588 and keep it from going to a vote in the Washington State House of Representatives. Universal background checks will do nothing but create a de facto registry of all transferred firearms, create a larger federal bureaucracy, and infringe upon the natural right of Washingtonians to own firearms. 

A Universal Background Check System would not stop criminals from getting their hands on firearms because criminals do not follow laws! All a criminal would have to do is get together with another criminal and sell a firearm without a background check. The law is inherently unenforceable! The only thing that this law does is put every firearms transfer in our state under the thumb of the federal government, allowing them to create a de facto registry of all transferred firearms. It would also make it difficult for people who live in rural areas to transfer firearms as many do not live near a registered FFL dealer. The fees associated with transferring firearms would also go up from their current average of $25 each. This could significantly impact Washingtonians' financial ability to purchase a firearm. 

Overall, this law does nothing to stop criminals and does everything to impede lawful Washingtonians from exercising their constitutional right to keep and bear arms. Please oppose House Bill 1588 and any other state or federal law that infringes upon the Constitution of The United States. Citizens like myself will not stand idly by and watch as our government strips away our natural, God-given rights. 



I am your constituent and I vote. Please represent me.


Sincerely,
